title.value: Leveraging Data Mining Algorithms to Recommend Source Code Changes
title.justification: It is the title of the paper provided.
title.quote: Leveraging Data Mining Algorithms to Recommend Source Code Changes

extractions.description: The paper proposes an automatic method for recommending source code changes using four data mining algorithms (Apriori, FP-Growth, Eclat, and Relim) and evaluates their performance empirically.

type.justification: The paper conducts an empirical evaluation to compare the performance of the data mining algorithms on source code change recommendation.
type.quote: we also conduct an empirical evaluation.

name.justification: The paper deals with recommending source code changes, which is within the realm of software engineering.
name.quote: Several works in the literature on software engineering have used development history to build data mining-based recommenders.

name.justification: The paper extensively uses data mining algorithms to recommend source code changes.
name.quote: Recent research has used data mining to develop techniques that can guide developers through source code changes.

name.justification: The focus of the paper is on recommending changes to source code.
name.quote: Recommending source code changes using four data mining algorithms.

name.justification: The Eclipse project is one of the datasets employed in the research for empirical evaluation.
name.quote: Our empirical study includes seven open-source projects: Eclipse, Elasticsearch, Rhino, SWT, Kotlin, Guava, and JabRef.
